hwL2VpnVplsExt.name: hwL2VpnVplsExt

revisions.description: The max length of hwVplsLdpPeerQosProfileName,hwVplsVsiQosProfileName changed from 31 to 63.
Add Leaf Nodes(hwL2vpnTnlType, hwL2vpnTunnelIndex) to hwVplsMIBObjects; Add OBJECT(hwL2vpnTnlType, hwL2vpnTunnelIndex) to VPLS MIB Trap(hwVplsVcDown).
add change reason Route Unreachable(89) Route Reachable(90)
Add trap nodes about VPLS VC limit alarm.

hwL2VpnVplsExt.contactinfo: Huawei Industrial Base Bantian, Longgang Shenzhen 518129 People's Republic of China Website: http://www.huawei.com Email: support@huawei.com
hwL2VpnVplsExt.description: The HUAWEI-VPLS-EXT-MIB contains objects to manage VPLS.

hwVplsTable.name: hwVplsTable
hwVplsTable.description: This table is the VPLS's configuration table. Users can create or delete the VSI by it.

hwVplsEntry.name: hwVplsEntry
hwVplsEntry.description: Provides the information of a VPLS entry.

hwVplsVsiName.name: hwVplsVsiName
hwVplsVsiName.description: This object indicates the VSI's name.

hwVplsSignal.name: hwVplsSignal
hwVplsSignal.description: This object indicates the signal type. If the signal type is LDP, VSI-ID must be designated. If the signal type is BGP, RD must be designated. The default value is unknown(255).

hwVplsRD.name: hwVplsRD
hwVplsRD.description: This object indicates the Route Distinguisher.

hwVplsVsiID.name: hwVplsVsiID
hwVplsVsiID.description: This object indicates the VSI id. The default value is 0.

hwVplsVcType.name: hwVplsVcType
hwVplsVcType.description: This object indicates the VC's encapsulation type.

hwVplsStatus.name: hwVplsStatus
hwVplsStatus.description: This object indicates the VPLS's status.

hwVplsMtu.name: hwVplsMtu
hwVplsMtu.description: This object indicates the VPLS's MTU.The default value is 1500.

hwVplsTunnelPolicy.name: hwVplsTunnelPolicy
hwVplsTunnelPolicy.description: This object indicates the tunnel policy.

hwVplsDescription.name: hwVplsDescription
hwVplsDescription.description: This object indicates the description information.

hwVplsLearnStyle.name: hwVplsLearnStyle
hwVplsLearnStyle.description: This object indicates the style of learning the MAC address.

hwVplsMacLearnEnable.name: hwVplsMacLearnEnable
hwVplsMacLearnEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of learning the MAC address.

hwVplsMacLimitEnable.name: hwVplsMacLimitEnable
hwVplsMacLimitEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of the MAC addresses number limit.

hwVplsStatisticsEnable.name: hwVplsStatisticsEnable
hwVplsStatisticsEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of statistics.

hwVplsUnknowMulticast.name: hwVplsUnknowMulticast
hwVplsUnknowMulticast.description: This object indicates the processing mode when the multicast MAC entry not found in FDB.

hwVplsUnknowUnicast.name: hwVplsUnknowUnicast
hwVplsUnknowUnicast.description: This object indicates the processing mode when the unicast MAC entry not found in FDB.

hwVplsPreference.name: hwVplsPreference
hwVplsPreference.description: This object indicates the preference.The default value is 0.

hwVplsVsiType.name: hwVplsVsiType
hwVplsVsiType.description: This object indicates the VSI's type.

hwVplsAdminVsiName.name: hwVplsAdminVsiName
hwVplsAdminVsiName.description: This object indicates the AdminVsi's name this VSI binding to

hwVplsAcIsolateFlag.name: hwVplsAcIsolateFlag
hwVplsAcIsolateFlag.description: This object indicates whether the AC in the VSI is isolated

hwVplsDiffServMode.name: hwVplsDiffServMode
hwVplsDiffServMode.description: Different service mode of the interface binding of vsi , default is uniform.

hwVplsDiffServServiceClass.name: hwVplsDiffServServiceClass
hwVplsDiffServServiceClass.description: PHB in the ingress PE, the value must be be,f1,af2,af3,af4,ef,cs6,cs7.The default value is invalidClass(255).

hwVplsDiffServColor.name: hwVplsDiffServColor
hwVplsDiffServColor.description: Remarked color of packet in the ingress PE, the value must be green,yellow,red.The default value is invalidColor(255).

hwVplsInterfaceWithdraw.name: hwVplsInterfaceWithdraw
hwVplsInterfaceWithdraw.description: Enable VSI send LDP mac-withdraw when VSI receive interface status changes event.

hwVplsUpe2NpeWithdraw.name: hwVplsUpe2NpeWithdraw
hwVplsUpe2NpeWithdraw.description: VSI forward message to all the NPE when VSI receive message from UPE.

hwVplsUpe2UpeWithdraw.name: hwVplsUpe2UpeWithdraw
hwVplsUpe2UpeWithdraw.description: VSI forward message to all the other UPE when VSI receive message from UPE.

hwVplsNpe2UpeWithdraw.name: hwVplsNpe2UpeWithdraw
hwVplsNpe2UpeWithdraw.description: VSI forward message to all the UPE when VSI receive message from NPE.

hwVplsDiscovery.name: hwVplsDiscovery
hwVplsDiscovery.description: This object indicates the discovery type. If the discovery type is static, the signal must be LDP. If the discovery type is auto, the signal must be BGP.

hwVplsMacWithdrawEnable.name: hwVplsMacWithdrawEnable
hwVplsMacWithdrawEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of the MAC address withdraw.

hwVplsVsiCir.name: hwVplsVsiCir
hwVplsVsiCir.description: This object indicates the committed information rate, based on VSI.

hwVplsVsiPir.name: hwVplsVsiPir
hwVplsVsiPir.description: This object indicates the peak information rate, based on VSI.

hwVplsVsiQosProfileName.name: hwVplsVsiQosProfileName
hwVplsVsiQosProfileName.description: This object indicates the QoS profile's name, based on VSI.

hwVplsAdminStatus.name: hwVplsAdminStatus
hwVplsAdminStatus.description: This object indicates the VSI's admin status.

hwVplsIgnoreAcState.name: hwVplsIgnoreAcState
hwVplsIgnoreAcState.description: This object indicates the enable sign of the ignorer of AC state.

hwVplsEnableStatistic.name: hwVplsEnableStatistic
hwVplsEnableStatistic.description: The enable sign of VSI's traffic statistics.

hwVplsAgingTime.name: hwVplsAgingTime
hwVplsAgingTime.description: The aging time of the VSI MAC address.

hwVplsUnknowUnicastMacLearning.name: hwVplsUnknowUnicastMacLearning
hwVplsUnknowUnicastMacLearning.description: The value of this object identifies whether the MAC address learning function for the discarded unknown unicast packets is enabled.

hwVplsFlowLabel.name: hwVplsFlowLabel
hwVplsFlowLabel.description: The value of this object identifies whether the PW FlowLabel is enabled.

hwVplsServiceName.name: hwVplsServiceName
hwVplsServiceName.description: The service name of the VSI

hwVplsRowStatus.name: hwVplsRowStatus
hwVplsRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this Table. Restriction: After the signal type, VSI ID and RD are configured, the configuration can not be modify or delete.

hwVplsRtTable.name: hwVplsRtTable
hwVplsRtTable.description: This table is the configuration table of VPN Target. Users can create or delete the VPN Target of a VSI.

hwVplsRtEntry.name: hwVplsRtEntry
hwVplsRtEntry.description: Provides the information of a RT entry.

hwVplsRtType.name: hwVplsRtType
hwVplsRtType.description: This object indicates the VC's encapsulation type.

hwVplsRtRowStatus.name: hwVplsRtRowStatus
hwVplsRtRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this Table. The max number of entries supported is 16. Not support modifying configuration.

hwVplsAcTable.name: hwVplsAcTable
hwVplsAcTable.description: This table is the configuration table of AC. Users can create or delete the AC of a VSI.

hwVplsAcEntry.name: hwVplsAcEntry
hwVplsAcEntry.description: Provides the information of a AC entry.

hwVplsAcIfIndex.name: hwVplsAcIfIndex
hwVplsAcIfIndex.description: This object indicates the interface index. There is only one VSI that can be created in one interface.

hwVplsAcStatus.name: hwVplsAcStatus
hwVplsAcStatus.description: This object indicates the AC's status.

hwVplsAcUpStartTime.name: hwVplsAcUpStartTime
hwVplsAcUpStartTime.description: Specifies the time this AC status has been Up(1).

hwVplsAcUpSumTime.name: hwVplsAcUpSumTime
hwVplsAcUpSumTime.description: Specifies the cumulate time this AC status has been Up(1).

hwVplsAcRowStatus.name: hwVplsAcRowStatus
hwVplsAcRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this Table. Not support modifying configuration.

hwVplsBgpInfoTable.name: hwVplsBgpInfoTable
hwVplsBgpInfoTable.description: This table is the configuration table of BGP information. Users can create or delete the BgpInfo entry.

hwVplsBgpInfoEntry.name: hwVplsBgpInfoEntry
hwVplsBgpInfoEntry.description: Provides the information of a BgpInfo entry.

hwVplsBgpInfoSiteID.name: hwVplsBgpInfoSiteID
hwVplsBgpInfoSiteID.description: This object indicates the site ID.

hwVplsBgpInfoOffset.name: hwVplsBgpInfoOffset
hwVplsBgpInfoOffset.description: Default original CE offset, default value is 0, calculate the VC in/out label.

hwVplsBgpInfoRowStatus.name: hwVplsBgpInfoRowStatus
hwVplsBgpInfoRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this Table. Restriction: Support creating only one entry currently. Before creating, the corresponding VSI's RD and signal type must be designated. The signal type must be BGP. Site can not be modified. Range can increase, but can't decrease.

hwVplsPwTable.name: hwVplsPwTable
hwVplsPwTable.description: This table is the configuration table of PW. Users can create or delete the PW entry.

hwVplsPwEntry.name: hwVplsPwEntry
hwVplsPwEntry.description: Provides the information of a PW entry.

hwVplsPwID.name: hwVplsPwID
hwVplsPwID.description: This object indicates the PW ID.

hwVplsPwRemoteIp.name: hwVplsPwRemoteIp
hwVplsPwRemoteIp.description: This object indicates the IP address of the remote end.

hwVplsPwTnlPolicy.name: hwVplsPwTnlPolicy
hwVplsPwTnlPolicy.description: This object indicates the tunnel policy.

hwVplsPwType.name: hwVplsPwType
hwVplsPwType.description: This object indicates the PW type.

hwVplsPwIsUpe.name: hwVplsPwIsUpe
hwVplsPwIsUpe.description: This object indicates the VPLS is UPE or not.

hwVplsPwInboundLabel.name: hwVplsPwInboundLabel
hwVplsPwInboundLabel.description: This object indicates the inbound label.

hwVplsPwOutboundLabel.name: hwVplsPwOutboundLabel
hwVplsPwOutboundLabel.description: This object indicates the outbound label.

hwVplsPwStatus.name: hwVplsPwStatus
hwVplsPwStatus.description: This object indicates the PW's status.

hwVplsPwVrIfIndex.name: hwVplsPwVrIfIndex
hwVplsPwVrIfIndex.description: This object indicates the VRRP interface this PW binding to.

hwVplsPwVrID.name: hwVplsPwVrID
hwVplsPwVrID.description: This object indicates the VrID this PW binding to.

hwVplsPwUpStartTime.name: hwVplsPwUpStartTime
hwVplsPwUpStartTime.description: Specifies the time this PW status was Up(1).

hwVplsPwUpSumTime.name: hwVplsPwUpSumTime
hwVplsPwUpSumTime.description: Specifies the cumulate time this PW status has been Up(1).

hwVplsPwState.name: hwVplsPwState
hwVplsPwState.description: This object indicates the PW's state.

hwVplsPwWorkingState.name: hwVplsPwWorkingState
hwVplsPwWorkingState.description: This object indicates the PW's working state.

hwVplsPwRowStatus.name: hwVplsPwRowStatus
hwVplsPwRowStatus.description: RowStatus for this Table. Restriction: Not support creating or modifying entry currently. If the signal type is LDP, we can delete PW by deleting Peer. If the signal type is BGP, we can delete PW by configuring RD. If the signal type is LDP, we need import PW ID value. If the signal type is BGP, we can import 0 as PW ID value.

hwVplsStatisticsTable.name: hwVplsStatisticsTable
hwVplsStatisticsTable.description: This table contains the VPLS's packets Statistic.

hwVplsStatisticsEntry.name: hwVplsStatisticsEntry
hwVplsStatisticsEntry.description: Provides the information of the VPLS's packets statistic.

hwVplsOutFrames.name: hwVplsOutFrames
hwVplsOutFrames.description: The total number of frames transmitted out of the VSI.

hwVplsInFrames.name: hwVplsInFrames
hwVplsInFrames.description: The total number of frames received on the VSI.

hwVplsOutBytes.name: hwVplsOutBytes
hwVplsOutBytes.description: The total number of bytes transmitted out of the VSI.

hwVplsInBytes.name: hwVplsInBytes
hwVplsInBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on the VSI.

hwVplsInDiscardFrames.name: hwVplsInDiscardFrames
hwVplsInDiscardFrames.description: The total number of frames received and then discarded on the VSI.

hwVplsUpDownNotifEnable.name: hwVplsUpDownNotifEnable
hwVplsUpDownNotifEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of VPLS notification. The default value is disable (2).

hwVplsStateChangeReason.name: hwVplsStateChangeReason
hwVplsStateChangeReason.description: This object indicates the reason of VC state change.

hwVplsLdpStatisticsTable.name: hwVplsLdpStatisticsTable

hwVplsLdpStatPwID.name: hwVplsLdpStatPwID
hwVplsLdpStatPwID.description: This object indicates the PW ID.

hwVplsLdpStatRemoteIpAddr.name: hwVplsLdpStatRemoteIpAddr
hwVplsLdpStatRemoteIpAddr.description: This object indicates the IP address of the remote end.

hwVplsLdpStatEnable.name: hwVplsLdpStatEnable
hwVplsLdpStatEnable.description: This object indicates the enable sign of LDP VPLS-PW's traffic statistics.

hwVplsLdpStatInTrafficRate.description: The traffic rate received on the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatOutTrafficRate.description: The traffic rate transmitted out of the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatInFrameRate.description: The rate of Frames received on the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatOutFrameRate.name: hwVplsLdpStatOutFrameRate
hwVplsLdpStatOutFrameRate.description: The rate of Frames transmitted out of the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatInBytes.description: The total number of bytes received on the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatOutBytes.name: hwVplsLdpStatOutBytes
hwVplsLdpStatOutBytes.description: The total number of bytes transmitted out of the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatInMulticastFrames.description: The total number of multicast frames received on the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatOutMulticastFrames.description: The total number of multicast frames transmitted out of the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatInBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of broadcast frames received on the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatOutBroadcastFrames.description: The total number of broadcast frames transmitted out of the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatInUnknowFrames.description: The total number of unknown frames received on the PW.

hwVplsLdpStatResetStatistic.name: hwVplsLdpStatResetStatistic
hwVplsLdpStatResetStatistic.description: Reset traffic statistics of VSI's LDP peer.

hwVplsBgpStatisticsTable.description: This table contains the VPLS-PW's Traffic Statistic.

hwVplsBgpStatisticsEntry.description: Provides the information of the VPLS-PW's Traffic Statistic.

hwVplsBgpStatSiteID.description: This object indicates the Site ID.

hwVplsBgpStatRemoteIpAddr.description: This object indicates the IP address of the remote end.

hwL2vpnTunnelIndex.name: hwL2vpnTunnelIndex
hwL2vpnTunnelIndex.description: This object indicates the mplsTunnelIndex. It contains an unused value for mplsTunnelIndex, or a zero to indicate that none exist. Negative values are not allowed, as they do not correspond to valid values of mplsTunnelIndex. Note that this object offers an unused value for an mplsTunnelIndex value at the ingress side of a tunnel. At other LSRs the value of mplsTunnelIndex SHOULD be taken from the value signaled by the MPLS signaling protocol.
